Found it. The problem is this line at the end:

```javascript
window.location.href = handleRootUrl(url);  // starts navigation
ToggleDisabled(true);
document.all.oProgressBar.style.display = "";
window.parent.location.reload(false);       // ← THIS cancels the navigation
```

`window.parent.location.reload(false)` reloads the parent frame immediately, which cancels (or overrides) the `window.location.href` navigation that was just initiated.

**Fix:** Remove or defer the parent reload. If you need the parent to reload after the import page loads, do it from `DataFileImport.asp` instead. For now:

```javascript
window.location.href = handleRootUrl(url);
ToggleDisabled(true);
document.all.oProgressBar.style.display = "";
// Remove: window.parent.location.reload(false);
```

If this page is inside an iframe and you actually want the *parent* to navigate instead:

```javascript
window.parent.location.href = handleRootUrl(url);
```

