messages.body:
Even so, `window.parent.location.reload(false)` is reloading your entire React app which destroys the iframe and cancels the navigation.

The simplest fix — just remove the parent reload when running inside the React app:

In the ASP page:
```javascript
window.location.href = handleRootUrl(url);
ToggleDisabled(true);
document.all.oProgressBar.style.display = "";

if (window.parent === window) {
    // Only reload parent in classic frameset, not when embedded in React
    window.parent.location.reload(false);
}
```

Or if the classic app uses a named frameset, check for that:
```javascript
if (window.parent && window.parent.frames.length > 1) {
    window.parent.location.reload(false);
}
```

Either way, the core fix is: **don't call `window.parent.location.reload(false)` when embedded in the React app's iframe**. It kills the iframe before navigation completes.

