messages.body:
Ah, so it's a popup window (or a new window) containing the iframe with the ASP page, not the main React app. In that case, `window.parent.location.reload(false)` reloads that popup window, which reloads the iframe back to `LoadDataFile.asp` — overriding your `window.location.href` navigation to `DataFileImport.asp`.

The fix is to swap the order — navigate first, don't reload the parent at all, or use a timeout:

```javascript
window.location.href = handleRootUrl(url);
ToggleDisabled(true);
document.all.oProgressBar.style.display = "";
// Remove: window.parent.location.reload(false);
```

Or if you truly need the parent window to reload *after* navigation completes, do it from `DataFileImport.asp` once it loads.

**Why it worked in classic:** In the classic app, the page was likely loaded directly in the window (not inside an iframe within the window). So `window.parent` was the same as `window`, and `reload(false)` had no effect since `window.location.href` was already navigating. Now that it's in an iframe, `window.parent` is the actual parent window, and reloading it destroys the iframe.

