So the debugger hits `window.location.href = handleRootUrl(url)` on line 291, but when you continue, the page reloads back to `LoadDataFile.asp` instead of navigating to `DataFileImport.asp`.

That confirms it — `window.parent.location.reload(false)` on line 294 is executing and reloading the parent window (which reloads the iframe back to `LoadDataFile.asp`) before the browser can complete the `window.location.href` navigation.

**Fix:** Remove or comment out line 294:

```javascript
window.location.href = handleRootUrl(url);
ToggleDisabled(true);
document.all.oProgressBar.style.display = "";
// window.parent.location.reload(false);  // ← remove this
```

You said the debugger doesn't hit 292/293/294 — that's because `window.location.href` on 291 starts an async navigation, but the JS engine still executes 292/293/294 synchronously before the navigation completes. The debugger may not pause on them if the parent reload (294) destroys the iframe first.

Try: put a `return;` right after line 291 and see if it navigates correctly:

```javascript
window.location.href = handleRootUrl(url);
return;
```

If that works, the problem is confirmed — line 294 is killing the navigation.
